---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const EFFECTIVE_DATE = "February 14, 2026";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — AOHSTD"
  description="Privacy Policy describing how AOHSTD processes information across its mobile applications and websites."
  active="privacy"
>
  <header class="policy-header">
    <span class="badge">Effective Date: {EFFECTIVE_DATE}</span>
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p>
      This Privacy Policy describes how AOHSTD (“we”, “our”, or “us”) collects,
      uses, processes, and discloses information when you use our mobile
      applications and websites (collectively, the “Services”).
    </p>
    <p>
      By accessing or using the Services, you acknowledge that you have read
      and understood this Privacy Policy.
    </p>
  </header>

  <div class="section" id="collect">
    <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p><b>A) Technical and Usage Information</b></p>
      <p>
        We may automatically collect certain technical information necessary
        to operate and improve the Services, including:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Device model and device identifiers</li>
        <li>Operating system version</li>
        <li>Application version</li>
        <li>Crash logs and diagnostics data</li>
        <li>Performance metrics</li>
        <li>Feature usage events</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We may use third-party service providers (such as Firebase or similar
        analytics and crash reporting tools) that process this information on
        our behalf.
      </p>

      <p><b>B) Subscription and Billing Information</b></p>
      <p>
        If a Service offers subscriptions or in-app purchases, payments are
        processed by platform providers (e.g., Google Play or Apple App Store).
        We do not collect or store full payment card details.
      </p>
      <p>
        We may receive limited information from the platform provider,
        such as subscription status, in order to enable or manage paid features.
      </p>

      <p><b>C) User-Submitted Content</b></p>
      <p>
        Some Services may allow you to submit content (such as images, files,
        or text). Where a feature requires server-side processing, your content
        may be uploaded and processed solely to provide the requested
        functionality.
      </p>
      <p>
        Content upload occurs only when you actively use a feature that
        requires such processing.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section" id="use">
    <h2>2. How We Use Information</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <ul>
        <li>Provide, operate, and maintain the Services</li>
        <li>Improve performance, stability, and user experience</li>
        <li>Monitor and prevent fraud, abuse, or security incidents</li>
        <li>Verify subscriptions and purchases</li>
        <li>Comply with legal obligations</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section" id="sharing">
    <h2>3. Disclosure of Information</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p>
        We do not sell personal information to advertisers or data brokers.
      </p>
      <p>
        We may disclose limited information to:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <b>Service providers</b> that assist with analytics, diagnostics,
          hosting, and infrastructure.
        </li>
        <li>
          <b>Platform providers</b> (e.g., Google or Apple) for billing and
          subscription processing.
        </li>
        <li>
          <b>Authorities</b> if required by law or to protect legal rights.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section" id="retention">
    <h2>4. Data Retention</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p>
        We retain information only for as long as necessary to provide the
        Services, maintain system integrity, comply with legal obligations,
        and resolve disputes.
      </p>
      <p>
        Retention periods may vary depending on the nature of the information.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section" id="security">
    <h2>5. Data Security</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p>
        We implement reasonable technical and organizational measures to
        safeguard information against unauthorized access, alteration,
        disclosure, or destruction.
      </p>
      <p>
        Data may be encrypted in transit and at rest where appropriate.
        However, no method of transmission or storage can be guaranteed to be
        completely secure.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section" id="international">
    <h2>6. International Data Transfers</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p>
        Information may be processed and stored in countries outside of your
        country of residence. By using the Services, you consent to such
        transfers where permitted by applicable law.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section" id="rights">
    <h2>7. Your Rights</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p>
        Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have rights to access,
        correct, delete, or restrict the processing of your personal
        information.
      </p>
      <p>
        To submit a request, please contact us at
        <a class="link" href="mailto:support@aohstd.com">
          support@aohstd.com
        </a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section" id="children">
    <h2>8. Children’s Privacy</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p>
        The Services are not directed to children under the age of 13 (or the
        equivalent minimum age in your jurisdiction). We do not knowingly
        collect personal information from children.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section" id="changes">
    <h2>9. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. The updated
        version will be indicated by the revised Effective Date above.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section" id="contact">
    <h2>10. Contact Information</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <p>
        If you have questions regarding this Privacy Policy, please contact:
      </p>
      <p>
        <a class="link" href="mailto:support@aohstd.com">
          support@aohstd.com
        </a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <footer class="footer">
    <div class="links">
      <a href="/">Home</a>
      <a href="/terms">Terms</a>
      <a href="mailto:support@aohstd.com">support@aohstd.com</a>
    </div>
    <small>© {new Date().getFullYear()} AOHSTD</small>
  </footer>
</BaseLayout>
